Week 3: Superstore Sales & Operations Dashboard (Power BI)
1. Objective
The objective of this project is to analyze retail business performance using the Superstore dataset and develop an interactive Power BI dashboard to generate insights across sales, profit, customers, regions, and logistics operations.

2. Tools Used
Power BI Desktop
DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)
Data Modeling & Visualization
3. Data Preparation & Modeling
The cleaned dataset prepared in Week 1 was loaded into Power BI. Additional transformations were performed to support advanced analysis.

-Calculated Columns:
Delivery Days
Expected Delivery Days
Delivery Status (On-Time / Delayed)
Customer Orders
Customer Type (Repeat / One-Time)
Discount Bins
Profit Category

These columns enabled better segmentation and operational analysis.

Measures Created:
Total Sales
Total Profit
Profit Margin %
Total Orders
Number of Customers
Total Quantity Sold
Average Order Value
Profit per Order
Sales Growth %
Average Delivery Days
Customer Contribution %
On-Time Orders
Delayed Orders
On-Time Delivery %
Number of Products
Profit Contribution %

These measures allow dynamic and interactive analysis across multiple business dimensions.

4. Dashboard Structure

The dashboard consists of five key pages:

- Executive Overview

Provides a high-level summary of business performance with key KPIs, sales trends, and profitability insights across categories and regions.

-Product Performance Analysis

Analyzes product-level performance, identifying top-performing and loss-making products, along with sub-category contribution to profit.

-Customer Insights

Focuses on customer behavior and contribution, including segmentation, repeat vs one-time customers, and customer profitability.

-Regional Performance

Examines geographical performance by analyzing sales, profit, and margin across regions and states, including identification of loss-making areas.

-Logistics & Operations

Evaluates delivery performance, shipping efficiency, and operational delays, along with their impact on profitability.

-5. Visualization Approach

The dashboard includes a mix of:

KPI Cards for key metrics
Bar Charts for comparisons
Line Charts for trends
Scatter Plots for relationships
Donut Charts for distributions

Interactive slicers (Year, Category, Region, Ship Mode) were used to enable dynamic filtering and deeper analysis.

6. Key Business Insights
Sales show an overall increasing trend, but profitability is impacted by high discounts
Some high-sales products generate low or negative profit
A small group of customers contributes significantly to total revenue
Certain regions have high sales but lower profit margins
Standard Class shipping has longer delivery times and contributes more to delays
Delivery delays can negatively impact profitability and operational efficiency

7. Business Recommendations
Reduce excessive discounting to improve profit margins
Review and optimize loss-making products
Focus on retaining high-value customers
Improve performance in low-profit regions through cost optimization
Enhance shipping efficiency, especially for Standard Class
Monitor and reduce delivery delays to improve customer satisfaction
8. Conclusion
This dashboard provides a comprehensive and interactive view of business performance across multiple dimensions. It enables better decision-making by identifying key trends, inefficiencies, and opportunities for improvement.
